olive oil
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet pork mince
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet Peri Peri Sauce
1 avocado
½ lemon
1 packet Corn Chips
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet garlic aioli
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag coriander
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Drain the sweetcorn
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat
• Cook pork mince, spice blend,
garlic paste and corn, tossing, until
browned, 3-5 mins
• Remove pan from heat and stir
through peri peri sauce

• Cut avocado in half, scoop out flesh
and chop. Halve the lemon
• Crush corn chips
• In a bowl, combine slaw and aioli

• Microwave tortillas on a plate
in 10 second bursts, until
warmed through
• Fill tortillas with slaw, pork
and avocado
• Top with cheese, torn coriander and
crushed corn chips
• Squeeze over lemon juice. Serve with
remaining lemon